    "scope": "D1",
    "claim_type": "concept",
    "status": "active",
    "claim": "Security controls have two orthogonal classification dimensions: Category (what they are made of) — Technical, Administrative, or Physical; and Function (what they do) — Preventive, Detective, Corrective, Deterrent, or Compensating. A single control can belong to both (e.g., firewall = technical + preventive).",
